quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  106,1,"For the accustomed security of the Quraysh,"
  106,2,"secure in their winter and summer journeys."
  106,3,"Let them worship the Lord of this [Sacred] House,"
  106,4,"Who fed them against hunger and made them secure against fear."
  107,1,"Have you seen the one who denies the Recompense?"
  107,2,"Such is the one who repulses the orphan harshly,"
  107,3,"and does not urge others to feed the needy."
  107,4,"So woe to those who pray,"
  107,5,"but are heedless of their prayer;"
  107,6,"those who only show off,"
  107,7,"and withhold even the small kindnesses."
  108,1,"We have surely given you [O Prophet] al-Kauthar [i.e., abundance],"
  108,2,"so pray and offer sacrifice to your Lord alone."
  108,3,"Indeed, the one who hates you is truly cut off [from all goodness]."